               <p>Second London Jury, Before Mr. Recorder.</p>
               <p>140. 
               
                  <persName id="t18331128-135-defend1395" type="defendantName">
                     MARCUS 
                     BERKMAN
                  <interp inst="t18331128-135-defend1395" type="surname" value="BERKMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-defend1395" type="given" value="MARCUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-defend1395" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-defend1395" type="age" value="20"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
             was indicted for <rs id="t18331128-135-off753" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-off753" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-off753" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18331128-135-cd754" type="crimeDate">11th of November</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-135-off753 t18331128-135-cd754"></join>, at St. Botolph, without, Aldgate, 3 necklaces, value 19s.; 12 pairs of spectacles, value 7s.; 60 pairs of ear-rings, value 6l.; 12 brooches, value 1l. 8s.; 17 shirt-pins, value 1l. 10s.; 4 pencil-cases, value 4s.; 18 thimbles, value 10s., and 1 wooden-box, value 15s., the goods of 
                     
                        <persName id="t18331128-135-victim1397" type="victimName">
                           Samuel 
                           Jacobs
                        <interp inst="t18331128-135-victim1397" type="surname" value="Jacobs"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18331128-135-victim1397" type="given" value="Samuel"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18331128-135-victim1397" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-135-off753 t18331128-135-victim1397"></join>
                     </persName>
                     
                  , in the dwelling-house of 
                     <persName id="t18331128-135-person1398">
                        Meyer 
                        Oppenheim
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1398" type="surname" value="Oppenheim"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1398" type="given" value="Meyer"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1398" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  
               
                  </rs>.</p>
               <p>The prisoner being a foreigner had the evidence interpreted to him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331128-135-person1399">
                  SAMUEL 
                  JACOBS
               <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1399" type="surname" value="JACOBS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1399" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1399" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18331128-135-viclabel755" type="occupation">licensed hawker, and deal in jewellery</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-135-victim1397 t18331128-135-viclabel755"></join>. I have known the prisoner some time; I saw him last year, and I saw him at Oxford once; I first saw him a twelvemonth ago - I went to live at No. 10, <placeName id="t18331128-135-crimeloc756">Ebenezer-square, in the city</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18331128-135-crimeloc756" type="placeName" value="Ebenezer-square, in the city"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18331128-135-crimeloc756" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-135-off753 t18331128-135-crimeloc756"></join>, a month ago next Friday; the prisoner came there on the following day; he slept in the same room with me - I had a box containing valuable articles; I delivered it to the landlady to keep for me; the landlady slept in the same room as the box was in - I went to the synagogue on the following Monday; I was going into the country afterwards - I missed my box at eight o'clock on the 11th of November; it contained the property stated in the indictment, which was worth 20l. altogether; the seals were worth 2l.; the ear-rings were worth 5l. 10s.; I am sure they were worth more than 5l. - I have since seen the box; this is it (looking at it) - I have got back all the property except what the pawnbroker has, which is one necklace.</p>

               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331128-135-person1400">
                  MEYER 
                  OPPENHEIM
               <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1400" type="surname" value="OPPENHEIM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1400" type="given" value="MEYER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1400" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at No. 10, Ebenezer-square, I don't know what parish it is in. Jacobs lodged in my house every time he came to London, and did so in November last; the prisoner also lodged in the same room at the same time - Jacobs delivered his box of trinkets to me to keep; I saw it last on Sunday night; I don't know the day of the month - I went to the synagogue at seven o'clock on Monday morning; the prisoner was then in the same room as I was; I left him there - Jacobs asked me for his box at eight o'clock on Monday morning and it was gone, and the prisoner had left the house; he never returned to the house of his own accord; he owed me 2s.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331128-135-person1401">
                  ANN 
                  ROSE
               <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1401" type="surname" value="ROSE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1401" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1401" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live with Mrs. Mullet, in Leman-street. I saw the prisoner on Monday, the 11th of November, at Mrs. Mullet's, between ten and eleven o'clock in the morning; he asked if Mrs. Mullet had a room to let; he spoke in English; I thoroughly understood him; Mrs. Mullet appeared to understand him; she spoke to him in English - she said she had a room, but it was empty, and she did not think it would suit him, but she could not accommodate him with a bed - he said then he should like to see the room, and he would go out in the afternoon and buy a bed - he had this box with him when he came; he said he had lost the key of his box and could not open it; he asked Mrs. Mullet if she could give him anything that could open the box - Mrs. Mullet said no, she had nothing; and she said then she would lend him a long nail; he then went up-stairs into the room - I went up immediately after and saw the box open in the room - he asked me if I would pledge four rows of coral beads for him, because he had no money about him; I did so; I pawned them at Mr. Sowerby's, in Cable-street, for 5s.; I gave the money to the prisoner - I did not see him open the box; the prisoner afterwards gave me a pair of ear-rings; I gave them up to the officer afterwards - I saw several articles inside the box, I could not see what they were; I saw ear-rings, beads, spectacles, thimbles, and a good many articles - there were a good many ear-rings, I could not see what number; I saw some shirt-pins, pencil-cases, combs, and a black necklace - the prisoner was taken in custody on Monday night, between ten and eleven o'clock.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331128-135-person1402">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SOWERBY
               <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1402" type="surname" value="SOWERBY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1402" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1402" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live at No. 81, Cable-street. I received a hank of beads in pledge from Ann Rose, for 5s.; I have them here - it was on Monday, the 11th of November; I knew her before, as dealing at the shop.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18331128-135-person1403">
                  CHARLES 
                  PALMER
               <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1403" type="surname" value="PALMER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1403" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-person1403" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . (policeman H 83). I apprehended the prisoner in a second-floor front-room, in Leman-street, between ten and eleven o'clock on the 11th of November - he asked me what I wanted before he opened the door; I told him my business was respecting a box of jewellery; he replied that he knew nothing about it - I found the box in the same room; this is it, and it contained the articles which are now in it - I searched him and found two pairs of coral earrings, the duplicate of the coral necklace, and 2s., on him; and as I was bringing him out of the house, the prosecutor came in and claimed the articles; Rose came up and gave me the ear-rings - the box had been broken open; I asked if he had the key; he said he had not got it - I know Ebenezer-square, it is in the parish of St. Botolph, without, Aldgate.(Property produced and sworn to).</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18331128-135-verdict757" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-verdict757" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 20. - <rs id="t18331128-135-punish758" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18331128-135-punish758" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18331128-135-defend1395 t18331128-135-punish758"></join>
               Transported for Life
            </rs>.</p>
